To optimize the MPI+OpenMP blocked GEMM with overlap of communication and compute, we can follow the following steps:

1. Define the MPI+OpenMP parallelization strategy:
   - Define the number of MPI processes (nproc) and the number of threads per process (ntp) using the MPI_Comm_size and MPI_Comm_rank functions.
   - Define the overlap factor (overlap) using the MPI_Comm_split function.

   ```c++
   int nproc, ntp;
   MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &nproc);
   MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &ntp);
   double overlap = 0.5; // Overlap factor

   M

